@node what "What is CP?"
@next features
@prev main
@{b}
CP is the most advanced, feature-packed kid's package currently available on
any system.
@{ub}
That is what they will say when the full version is released!!

Incorporating full-screen animation with an advanced GUI and full
customisation, CP truly represents the ultimate in children's software.

Add a wealth of fun-packed features and you can't help wondering why
something this great hasn't been done before!

CP is currently at version 0.206, with the great 0.25 under construction.

Only the paint package side of the software is available at this stage, but
more and more parts of the system will be included as version after version
is released.

Just take a look at the section @{"features" link Features} to see why CP represents a new era
in software childrens software.
@{b}
PLEASE NOT THAT CP IS SHAREWARE AND AS SUCH, HAS CERTAIN RESTRICTIONS.
TO REMOVE THESE RESTRICTIONS YOU MUST @{" REGISTER " link regi}.

N.B. IF YOU USE THIS PREVIEW VERSION AT ALL YOU MUST AT LEAST SEND AN E-MAIL
TO US WITH YOUR COMMENTS ABOUT THE PROGRAM.
@{ub}
@endnode

@node Features "CP's Main Features"
@next requirements
@prev what

Please note that this section mainly refers to the features of the
FINISHED version of CP.  As each new version is completed, they will
become more and more like the descriptions below.

@{b}
Advanced Interface@{ub} *************************************************

When finished, CP will have the most advanced interface ever created
on ANY platform.

Its incredible GUI will be very easy to use and understand while
remaining extremely responsive.

A major feature of CP's intuitive interface will be the revolutionary
use of amazing full-screen animations to perform almost every task.

The use of animation means that children can enjoy a level of
interaction with the software never seen before in any other program.

Imagine being able to interact with the very characters that guide you
through the software... asking them what a certain button does, getting
them to do some crazy acts or even tickling them with your mouse and
chasing them round the screen!

No other software has ever attempted to achieve this level of
interaction and enjoyment before. It will truly be the ultimate activity
and learning environment for kids!!

@{b}
Fully Customisable!@{ub} ************************************************

Another great feature of CP is its ability to configure itself according
to whoever is using the program.

Almost every aspect of the software can be configured, helping to
ensure that children using the software will have the best experience
possible.

The easy to use preferences program covers such topics as Users,
Graphics, System, Tools, Music/Sound and User's Skill, all with many
individual options.

This means that the software can adjust perfectly to whoever is using it,
right down to the way things are displayed, how tasks are performed
and what the users are limited to doing!!

@{b}
Exceptionally Intelligent@{ub} ******************************************

CP just goes from strength to strength!!
Tying all CPs great features together is the incredibly intelligent
internal system routines designed to help the user get the best out
of the software with minimum fuss and maximum efficiency.

Once completed, they should be able to cope with most errors in such
a fluid fashion that the user won't even have to be alerted as to what
has happened.

This is all part of Mystique's great concept that the user should be
hidden from the internal workings as much as possible so that he/she
may get on with actually using and enjoying the software.

@{b}
Great Graphics@{ub} *****************************************************

CP is very graphic intensive and has an excellent, easy-to-use GUI
that your children will love.

Great care has been taken to make sure that the GUI's layout is as
simple and effective as possible.

The children can even choose from a set of different themed GUIs
including standard, paint, army, flowers and cartoons!! (With possibly
more to come).

@{b}
Great Sound@{ub} ********************************************************

No fully interactive animated interface would be complete without a
great sound system.

CP will have sounds for every function and animation giving the whole
program a more involving feeling for the children.

Several musical tracks will be written for the software to suit a number
of different tastes in background music!

@{b}
Plenty To Do!@{ub} ******************************************************

CP will be a full suite of software for kids incorporated into one package
- a kind of one-stop shop!!

Currently it consists only of an early version of the Paint package but
will go on to include many games, utilities and educational programs, all
fluidly integrated into the one great package!!

@{b}
Fantastic Help System@{ub} **********************************************

An integral part of the interface will be the online help system available
at any time.

Interactive animations will be used to help explain any features not
understood ensuring that children won't need anyone beside them
while they use the program.

@{b}
Comprehensive Documentation@{ub} ****************************************

CP will come with a full colour user's guide filled with helpful tips and
examples all presented with a great graphic design.

It will also have full HTML documentation with many screenshots and
pictures to aid your exploration of this great software!


********************************************************************
********************************************************************
@{b}
The current version of CP already incorporates the following features
quite extensively....
@{ub}

Configuration ******************************************************

Each user has their own preference file which contains details about..

 · Their name.

 · The sample to be used for their name. (You need a sound sampler for this).

 · Their ability - For example, whether the right mouse button performs a
                   different function or not.

 · Disk Access - Whether or not they can load/save (or even format disks) and
                 which type of file requestor they can use - simple, advanced
                 or workbench (ASL).

 · Color Selection - Whether they use a scrolling palette with large icons
                     for younger children or a standard DPaint style palette.

 · Tools - You can even restrict the amount of tools that the user has access
           to!! This means that you can set up CP so that only the older
           children can use certain tools.

 · Icons - Each child can either can use all the "stickers" or their own
           particular sets - e.g. war, space, animals, cartoons etc.!!

 · GUI - There will be a number of GUIs to choose from - paint, flowers,
         shapes (the standard interface) and war. (+ possibly even more!!).

 · Screen Blanking - CP has its own screen blanker built-in which will have
                     many different, often humourous animations. Each user
                     can have a blanker selected for them according to their
                     taste.

 · Sound/Music - CP will come with many tracks of stereo sound and plenty of
                 amusing samples to keep your children happy all the time!!

 · Graphics - You can control how fast animations are, choose between
              different types of scrolling all for that personal touch!!


GUI ****************************************************************

CP is full of great graphics... It uses a huge variety of wipes and
animations to aid enjoyment of the program as well as to help the user!!
A Major hit with all the children so far!!


Colour Effects *****************************************************

CP has multiple color cycling modes!! CP's tools can all be used with
special graphics modes that transform the way they work giving you even more
options!!


IO *****************************************************************

CP contains the most advanced loading/saving routines for chidren known to
man!! These routines are so simple to use yet they are unbelievably complex!!
They look great, feel great and cope with a huge amount of errors so that
all the children need to do in the easiest routines is to click on the
picture they want to paint and you know that they will rarely have a problem!


Memory Handling ****************************************************

CP has an amazing UNDO and memory system which will adapt to ever setup
to make the most efficient use of what its got. CP's undo system can even
resize screens so that the program will never quit!!


@endnode

@node requirements "Requirements"
@next install
@prev features

This version of CP should run on any Amiga® computer or compatible OS
from Workbench® v1.3+ with 1MB+ of RAM and a Hard-drive.


Future versions will require:

* Workbench 3.x
* AGA or Gfx Card
* 1.5MB RAM

@endnode

@node install "Installation"
@next usage
@prev requirements

If downloaded from the internet, CP comes as a .lha file. To extract this
file, move it to the directory you would like the files extracted to, double
click on its icon and type:

 @{fg shine}"lha x cp.lha"@{fg text} and all the files will be extracted to that directory.


CP comes with a hard-drive install script that uses the standard Commodore®
Installer Version 43.3.

Simply double click on the icon "Install_CP" and follow the onscreen prompts.

If any errors occur during installation, the script will try to alert you of
the problem encountered and will normally give you some options to choose
from.

If, for any reason, the installation is aborted mid-way or a serious error
was encountered, all installed files will be removed from your hard drive.
If this happens, please try installation in a different directory on your
hard-drive.  If you are having serious problems installing CP, please write
or e-mail: @{" Contact " link contact}
@endnode

