@node bugs "Bugs"
@next history
@prev contact
@{b}
Current notable bugs/limitations.
@{ub}
CP Version 0.206 will not cause your system to crash.  However, in the
unlikely event of some hack causing CP to fail, please @{" contact " link contact} us.

The name selection screen "OTHER" does not yet work properly. It won't do
any harm, but we advise against its use.

CP's system files must all be kept intact.  If any of the CP files are
deleted, CP may not be able to run.  This limitation will be removed in
a future version of CP.

@endnode

@node History
@next future
@prev bugs
                            The HIStory Of CP
                         -----------------------

CP has been in development now since 1993.  It has gone through some amazing
transformations in the past few years and will be going through many more
over the next year.

@{fg shine}
Changes since CP Version 0.1
@{fg text}
@{b}
Version 0.15@{ub} ____________________________________________________________

PERFECTED SCROLLING!!! CP has a new advanced scrolling mechanism which
scrolls fluidly on all set-ups. Scroll speeds are exactly the same now, no
matter what tool you are using!!

NTSC compatibility introduced. CP now adapts (crudely) for NTSC users.

Better graphics. CP has had some changes to some of its graphics with even a
few extra screens!!

Other minor improvements. (Samples have been allocated properly among other
things).

@{b}Version 0.16@{ub} ____________________________________________________________

Fixed bugs in "Load Picture" which caused CP to quit.

Also enhanced the look of the "Load Picture" routine.

Added "Please Wait" dialogue box to the Control Menu to alert users that the
delay on leaving the control menu is meant and not an error.

Added "Pick A Picture To Load" Text to loading routines.

Fixed bug in installer which meant CP would only install to a directory on
a hard drive, not on the root volume.



@{b}Version 0.20@{ub} ____________________________________________________________

Updated the intro sequence with better, more linear graphics (no messy
multiple screens).

Updated MOST other graphics to a more pleasing, three-D effect.

Added new pictures to the Main and IO menus.

Introduced a keyfile system to reward people who send an E-Mail.

Added 2 new Preference sections covering:

  Users' Names
  Users' Samples (Not Yet Implemented - NYI)
  No. of Users
  Method for name selection (NYI)

  Mouse Use
  Help Menu On/Off (NYI)
  Startup Options
  Color selection methods
  Keyboard Enabled/Disabled (Partly implemented - use advised AGAINST!!)

Added other minor system fixes.

Created new fonts and adapted program for their use.

Created two small, very basic (Crap!!) anims, just to give users something to
look at.

Updated the Installer File (now works perfectly).

Removed the need for a CPSYSPREFS file to be in your S: drawer, CP now uses
a system assign.



@{b}Version 0.205@{ub}___________________________________________________________

Added a full help system to the preferences section of the program.

Added a NEW Preference section which allows the person setting up the program
to choose which tools their children are allowed access to.

Each tool now has a difficulty rating which parents can use as a guide to
choosing tools for their children.

Added new drawing mode for younger users(2-4) which means that, to draw, they
only have to click to start drawing and click to stop drawing!

Added a NEW, partly-finished Preference section which currently only covers
disc access issues.
You can now select how much disc access the current user should be given.
Covers such things as loading and saving and the selection of disks.

Restored full NTSC compatibility (Temporarily abandonded for Version 0.20!).

Added many more wipes to the Preference section making its use much more
fluid!!

Fixed up the sticker menu - now the stickers update properly on screen.
Also fixed a bug which wouldn't let users pick a new sticker until they had
scrolled through the bank of stickers.

Finally got rid of the bug that caused CP to quit if a screen size of less
than 400 was selected - screen sizes right from 336 pixels wide can now be
selected.

Updated the ending sequence of the program.

Other minor system changes, modifications and extras.



@{b}Version 0.206@{ub}___________________________________________________________

Minor release to update a few parts of Version 0.205 while the conversion
to C code is taking place.

Updated Documentation covering Registration details and the future Features,
Specs and Limitations of CP.

Crude fix of Naming Routines when 'Other' is selected.  Graphics still
distorted somewhat, but overall function much clearer and reliable now :)

Updated some text in the software, specifically the registration/restriction
details and the Copyright Notices/Contact Addresses.

Mystique Incorporated as:

@{b}Mystique Corporation International Ltd@{ub}

New logo and text added to software to represent change.


Work on next big version change progressing well.....


@{b}Now check out CP's @{" future " link future}
It's much more exciting... @{ub}

@endnode

@node future "What's to come...!!"
@next orderform
@prev history

As the list of @{" features " link features} shows, CP's future is looking bright!

CP is modular and the bulk of the work has already been done. It is very open
so lots more features can be added without affecting the current code. This
also means that, since the new code won't affect the old, the older code can
be continually refined without having to refine all the new modules as well.
And that is good news for you...

Because this means that CP can only get better. The older modules can only
become more advanced and the new modules can only add to the fun experience
that is CP.

We can see the end of the road however - CP Version 3.0 in a world where
Gateway 2000 got the balance right (i.e. R&D + Advertising), the Power Amiga
controls most of the devices in our homes and the major development in going
from CP Version 2.0 to 3.0 is voice recognition! Roll on 23 June 2000!!

However, on a more serious note...
@{b}
NEW features of CP version 0.25:
@{ub}
* Being written in C code for 68K and possibly even PowerPC - dramatic speed
increase!!

* Full localization.

* RTG support - if you have a monitor, CP will now be promoted.

* Extra features - all of the suggestions over the past three months will
  be implemented - a huge number of add ons!!

* Full Preferences control - at long last, CP will be fully configurable.

* IFF support.

* Full HTML Docs (Registered version only).

* Animations - the first (preliminary) animations will be added.

* And many more enhancements in what will be CP's greatest update yet!!

  

@endnode

