@node cpassign "Assigning CP"
@next main
@prev disclaimer

CP needs an assign in S:User-startup to run properly.

The installer modifies the file S:User-startup to assign CP when your
machine is booted.

For this assign to work, you must reboot after installing CP.


If you DIDN'T and you got the message @{fg shine}CP needs an assign@{fg text} then you should
reboot now.


If you DID reboot after installing CP, then the installer may have been
unable to add an assign in your S:User-startup file.

To add an assign in the user-startup file, follow these steps:

Open the file @{fg shine}S:Startup-sequence@{fg text} with a text editor and look for the line;

                       @{fg shine}Execute S:User-startup@{fg text}

If this line is not there, add it BEFORE LoadWB

Now, if the file @{fg shine}S:User-startup@{fg text} exists, add the following line to it;

                        @{fg shine}Assign CP: *****:????/CP/CP@{fg text}

(Where *****:???? is the directory where the main folder CP is installed)

Otherwise create a new file, add the above line, then save this new file as
@{fg shine}S:User-startup@{fg text}.

Reboot, and enjoy CP!!

If you need any help, just @{" contact " link contact} us.


@endnode
